                {
                    "type": "nodes.speak",
                    "id": "17afc77b-84c6-46e0-b868-735d42e4a349",
                    "actorId": "6b30a3a9-2324-487d-9db9-03ce174e0e80",
                    "actorId2": null,
                    "text": "Today, we are going to discuss bandages and how to use them to prevent further damage to a wound. I suggest that you always carry a set of bandages everywhere - you never know when you might need some.",
                    "emotion": "0",
                    "emotion2": "0",
                    "device": "0",
                    "device2": "0"
                },
                {
                    "type": "nodes.speak",
                    "id": "50f77a9d-5d9f-40fd-aff5-528a44402df4",
                    "actorId": "6b30a3a9-2324-487d-9db9-03ce174e0e80",
                    "actorId2": null,
                    "text": "First, you will need to know how to make an effective bandage - the type of material, the care and cleaning of the material, and the proper sizes. ",
                    "emotion": "0",
                    "emotion2": "0",
                    "device": "0",
                    "device2": "0"
                },
                {
                    "type": "nodes.speak",
                    "id": "e67c3739-9456-4c7a-9a85-3c06f3116aa7",
                    "actorId": "6b30a3a9-2324-487d-9db9-03ce174e0e80",
                    "actorId2": null,
                    "text": "Then we will talk about how to wrap wounds, sprains, and even temporarily treat broken bones.",
                    "emotion": "0",
                    "emotion2": "0",
                    "device": "0",
                    "device2": "0"
                },
                {
                    "type": "nodes.speak",
                    "id": "99c53420-40c8-425b-949c-4ccac2a6cbaf",
                    "actorId": "6b30a3a9-2324-487d-9db9-03ce174e0e80",
                    "actorId2": null,
                    "text": "Does anyone have any questions or comments before we get started?",
                    "emotion": "1",
                    "emotion2": "0",
                    "device": "0",
                    "device2": "0"
                },
                {
                    "type": "nodes.showMenu",
